configset  GLOBAL  latchkey_lifetime = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : 60
Data Type     : integer
Category      : access
Password Notes: Visible only with password. Set with global password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset GLOBAL latchkey_lifetime = 30


The number of minutes for which a temporary password
(latchkey) remains valid.  Latchkeys are used by the 
WWW interfaces to prevent permanent passwords being
cached by WWW client software.


See Also:
   help configset dup_lifetime
   help configset log_lifetime
   help configset post_limits
   help configset session_lifetime
   help configset token_lifetime
   help configset triggers

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
